	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am always amazed when peopel say shaman can't melee.&nbsp;&nbsp;I melee when soloing and, if needed I melee in a group. Melee classes are less comon at higher lvl, and I've gone on more than one guild hunt that was only doable because I could melee.  If you want to melee as shaman you need to work to keep your skill up.<br><br>You are right, do not use your Jade Chokdais Prod, get your self a good 2hb weapon.  By the upper 30's a JCP just dosent do enough damage.  <br><br>Also use your buffs, noone has better melee buffs than a shaman.  <br><br>IMHO kiting is not the best way for a shaman to kill.  Sure you can do it, but by doing it you do not keep your melee skills up.  Your dots only do 75% of there normal damage if your target is moving.  Kitting is a limited ability anyway.  There are limited places you can do it.  <br><br>Here is how I recomend you solo your shaman.  Cast Str, agi, dex on yourself.  Pull the mob with solw, dot the mob and beat it to death.  <br><br>When you get regen and speed cast these on yourself as well.  <br><br>When you get your pet buff it with str, dex and speed.  <br><br>I've gotten a number of nice items because I could solo the mob while staying in one place.<br><br>Keep your 2hb skill maxed.  A JCP is a very nice weapon until lvl 34 or so.  A mortificators staff is as good as the JCP.  A rune wood great staff is much better than a JCP, but what about the wisdom?  A JCP and a CGS at lvl 50 will give you 100 more mana points?  What are you going to cast with 100 mana points at lvl 50?  The damage done by a good 2hb is worth more than 100 mana points<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
