	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you go back and read some of the older posts, you will see I am a supporter of melee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Gorthin has a 200 offense, 200 defense, and 175 (all capped)in his main weapon.  However, once you hit a certain point, which can vary with you play style, you are better off meditating *when you are grouped*.<br><br>The damage output by a Shaman Melee wise at higher levels is not even worth mentioning.  Sure, with a big 2h blunt you can occasionally get a solid hit in.  As long as the situation is under control, and you are topped out on mana (which, IMO should almost never happen, will explain in a second), go ahead and stand up and whack that nasty a few times.  But I am seldom anywhere near FM.<br><br>Between buffing everyone, regenning the tanks, slowing the mobs, root parking extras, emergency healing, and all of the little things a shaman should be doing, a lot of times, the only time I stand up is to buff/cannabilize/heal =)  In this situation, every 6 seconds I am standing, is one less tick of mana I get back to continue casting.<br><br>If you have the situation in hand, meleeing is fun, and can be helpful.  It is also generally VERY low on aggro for us =)  Personally, if I want damage output though, I will cast a DoT and stay out of the way.  Or, if you prefer, that is what our pet is for.<br><br>As to the merits of a 2h blunt vs 1h plus a shield, do not forget the armor class.  Just as a clarification, a JCP+CGS at 50 is 150 more mana.  I use a JCP+Shield of Falsehood.  Yes it is less wisdom, but it is more ac.  If you can crack the ac barriers of 800, 900, etc without a shield, then pull out the big 2h blunt when you decide to fight.  Otherwise go for the AC.  It really helps when you get summoned after having two slows resisted, and you have to cast a third on the same mob.  Getting Quadded for 220 on an unslowed mob can hurt, really fast =)<br><br>Both ways have their merit, and neither is wrong.  IMO, having a shield and medditating outweighs the value of our melee after about level 40.  Keeping the skills up is a good idea though.  Nothing is more embarassing than getting attacked by a low green, and having to nuke it because you can't hit it.  And a maxed defense skill is a wonderful thing to have.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
