	   <tr><td colspan=2>For the most part I agree with what you are saying, as long as by grouped you mean in a full well balanced group.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even at lvl 48, I sometimes find myself in a group with only one tank.  Here is my rule for wheather to melee or not.  1 tank I melee, 2 tanks I might melee depending on what other classes are in the group and the lvl and class of the tanks.  3 tanks I do not melee.  <br><br>However with all do respect Gorthin, for I think you are one of the more enlightend spear toters, I don't think you understand the POWER of the 2HB.  Lets look at an example shaman who equiped with a CGS and a JCP has wis 175, AC 805.  Equiped with a Drakkel Icegrinder they would have Wis 160 and AC about 795.  The first has 8% more mana and 1 or 2% (sorry of the top of my head I don't know how much more actual ac you get from a +10 ac item) more ac.  However the seconed one will do 38% more damage, not including proc and str bonus.  When it is time to melee there is no way that 2% ac and 8% wis is going to match 38% more damage.  The fact is i can solo mobs with a 2hb that i can not solo with a one hand weapon and shild.  <br>You said that "the damage output by a shaman Melee wise at higher levels is not even worth mentioning", you also said that if you want damage output I will cast a dot.  From personal experance before lvl 49 there is not a dot you can cast that will consistantly out damage my Icegrinder.  You cast your dot and need to med to regain the mana used.  I could melee and do as much damage and still be FM.  I have also read that in groups most shaman will not cast the lvl 49 poision dot because of the amount of mana it uses, they also choos to cast the lower dot while grouped.  <br><br>From my expeance at higher lvls shaman can do meaningful damage meleeing, but only if they use a 2hb.  In a full, well balanced group casting a dot or meleeing with a 2hb will have about the same impact, but meding and casting is the expected behavor of a shaman.  But there are times in small groups or in unbalanced groups that it would be far better for the shaman to melee than to sit on his dark ember and watch the tank take a beating.  <br><br>The shaman is born a melee class and with each lvl becomes more and more a caster, and perhaps at some point becomes only a caster.  If this happens I don't know what lvl it happens at, but I am sure it doesn't happen before lvl 50.  Yes most of the power of the shaman comes from his spells, but the best shaman spell are for melee classes.  The shaman's magic lets him melee solo better than any other class.  <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
