	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey, alright, a civil discussion.&nbsp;&nbsp;I like that =)  I am glad you mentioned you vary your tactics depending on group makeup.  You would be suprised how man people do not.<br><br>I am not going to try to throw numbers out at you.  But let me point out as what I see as a couple of fallacies with yours.<br><br>The first is the magical 800 AC spot.  Learn it, love it, NEVER go below it if you can help it in anyway.  I was amazed how much of a difference damage wise I took by breaking 800 AC.  If you are 5 ac points away from cracking 800 AC, lose some wisdom (or get a shield *wink*) to break that barrier.  I do not use a shield for the mana per se.  I use it for the AC.  I do not have any hard numbers, but 795 AC vs 800 AC = approx a 20% damage difference received IMO.  It is absolutely insane how much less damage you take.<br><br>Your damage output melee wise will be higher than mine, sure.  But let me explain why I do not think it will matter.<br><br>Here is a typical setup.  Talisman for the Chanter, Cleric, main tank.  General buffs (usually stamina and strength, sometimes dex and agi) on tanks.  Sometimes speed on the tanks (if no chanter *shudder*).  Chloro the Chanter (every little bit helps) and main tanks.  Over the course of that, I have used, let's say, 60m.  We med, I Can/Chloro til around  70m to 80m, we charge in.<br><br>Fight breaks out.  I slow primary mob.  Chanter mezzes.  I slow secondary mob, chanter mezzes.  I slow tertiary mob.  I then root both additional mobs.  I sit and med.  Do an emergency heal.  Med some more.  Reroot third mob, and reslow.  Med.  We win *cheer*  I am at 45 to 50m (250 mana for a slow hurts...),sometime higher.  I proceed to canna/med.  Cleric is 60m+, so puller goes.  I slow, med.  Monster usually dies about the same time I manage to regain the slow mana.  In fact, the only time I get ahead is with C2, and chloro/canna.  Otherwise I break even.<br><br>Does that sound fairly realistic to you?  I hope so, otherwise the rest of my point won;t work =).  When am I gonna get time to melee?  As I melee, I fall further and further behind in the mana race, and that is not good.  If I fall too far behind by not managing my time wisely, I slow the group down.  And unless they are your friends, you will get booted.  Xp grind groups SUCK.  They are boring.  When you have to wait  on the Shaman to get mana back to do his job on top of it....  Or if you don't wait, and the Chanter croaks, game over.<br><br>That is why I do not melee.  Shaman are some of the most mana intensive casters over the course of a group.  Those buffs and all add up.<br><br>If you just want damage, sure, go for a 2h blunt.  Just make sure you fight the rogue for the backside of the mob =)  But if you want overall group efficiency, let your buffs and your pet do the damage for you.  It is not a matter that you can do as much damage with a weapon, it is keeping up with the mana curve.<br><br>Remember, these are my opinions, and I hope I clarified why I do not melee, at least not often.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB Maxed offense, pierce, and defense =)<br>Aka, I don't mind melee at all.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
