	   <tr><td colspan=2>In that group and with 3 mobs being pulled at a time I wouldn't melee either.&nbsp;&nbsp;And I agree Xp grind groups suck, that is why for the most part I avoid them.  <br><br>My experiance with the magical 800 AC has not been all that impressive.  I have an ac 15 shield I got off some giant in GD and a Dark Ember I use to keep my 1hb skill up.  With the Shield I am AC 811 with out it 796, or there about.  (I made the effort to get to AC 800 after reading some of your earily posts.)  Now the Dark Ember is a better melee weapon than the JCP. However I can kill mobs while using the Drakkel Icegrinder and while below 800AC that I can not kill using the Dark Ember and shild while above 800 AC. My weapons skill are nearly the same. I am willing to accept that 800 is a magical number, however My experiance indacates that the extra damage output you get from the Icegrinder more than makes up for any loss of mana or ac.  <br><br>Yes in the Xp grind groups, in groups chain pulling or pulling mutipul mobs you need to med, and there is little opertunity to melee. <br>I personaly don't spend much time in zones where this type of grouping is the norm.  And being a member of a guild that is low on tanks at the upper lvls I frequently tank on some of the guild hunts.  <br><br>For me the shaman is able to fill many roles, and shouldn't be limited to only a caster.  Yes there is a time and a place for casting and there is a time and place for melee.  The secret to sucess is knowing when to do which and being able to do both.  I have 4 or 5 items I carry with me and wear or hold to switch between melee and mana mode, or anywhere inbetween.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
