	   <tr><td colspan=2>Woe and Envy drop from the same mob.&nbsp;&nbsp;You must have both items (along with Marr's Promise) to obtain the Shield of Falsehood.  If, somewhere along the way, you can acquire the Woe and the Marr's Promise, you will not have to go to Rathe Mountains to get them.  Once you get the small gem from the spirit in Erud's Crossing, you go straight to the Wandering Spirit in western Karanas.  Give the spirit the gem.  Then give the spirit the Woe, Envy and Marr's Promise (all at once).  After you give the spirit these items, you must say "What Shield of Falsehood?"  and the spirit will give you the Shield of Falsehood on  your cursor and will drop a 'sparkling gem' into your inventory.  You then continue on with the Test of Might.   Good luck!!<br><br>I highly recommend you printing AND STUDYING the spoiler on the Spear of Fate quest on Belgar's Ultimate Guide to Alchemy site.<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>Oracle of Novus Invictus<br>(Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>51 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
