	   <tr><td colspan=2>Before you condemn folks hunting in the lower lvl dungeons, ask them WHY they are hunting there.&nbsp;&nbsp;CB and Blackburrows are zones that are frequently hunted by inappropriate lvls to obtain faction.  The best way for a dark race to get Qeynos faction is to hunt in Blackburrows.  Kill kill kill gnolls (till they are quite sick of them in fact), and collect gnoll fangs.  Once they kill enough to where they are "dubious" to Qeynos guards, they go on into town to turn in the fangs for even more faction.  Highpass is another area frequently hunted by higher lvls in order to get faction with the Freeport Militia.<br><br>It's not ALWAYS about exp, but rather the faction gained by hunting in these zones.  Believe me when I say that higher lvl players hunting in these zones for faction are not there having a good time.  Faction hunting is a time-consuming pain in the behind, and boring at best.  (also mention here that players hunting for faction should select "off times" for their little ventures...times of the day when noobs aren't out in force).<br><br>Now, as for the higher lvl players who insist on taking out the noobs' mobs without good reason, bah on them.  I agree that if you don't need the faction, and if you don't get exp for it, then you should be moving on to something that does.<br><br>(I won't go into farming/loot here.  Suffice it to say, the alchemist was green to me at lvl 48, and dammit, I needed that cloak.  So I killed it)<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>Oracle of Novus Invictus<br>(Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>51 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
