	   <tr><td colspan=2>At your lvl I think it is a mistake to assume that you can't out damage your dots with a good weapon, and lvl maxed melee skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;At lvl 48 I do as much damage with my weapon in the same amount of time as I do with my poision dot. <br><br>I personaly think that it is a mistake for shaman not to melee when soloing.  Shaman have good melee stats and have some very nice weapons.  <br><br>However the things is shaman can be played a number of diffrent ways and how am i to say witch is best.  As for as your plans for the future go you should know that if you kite your dots will only do 75% of there normal damage.  And as you pointed out if you root the mob it will kill your pet.  Therefore if you want to use the pet while soloing you have two choices.<br>1. Buff and heal the pet, inculding speed and regen, while it kills the rooted mob.  <br>2. Buff yourself and the pet while killing the unrooted mob.  <br><br>I perfer the seconed choice.  I cast speed, str, and sometime dex on the pet.  I cast speed, regen, adi, shild, sta, str, dex, and tuna on myslef.  Yes that is a lot of buffs but they last along time except for regen and speed.  I ues the best ratio 2hb i can get my hands on.  After a low blew kill I have most my health and 3 bubbles of mana, I dont cast the sickness dot on lower lvl mobs.  After a mid blue kill I maybe as low as half health and half mana.  There are some blue cons and even cons I can't not kill with this methood.  But I can kill meleers, casters, and healers.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
