	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is more a personal opinion/comment really...<br><br>But, how many of you shammies out there just love giving those big dumb tanks the full set of your godlike buffs of love? Seeing their eyes light up when they're blinded by a whole screen covered with stat buffs speed buffs better vision etc. (yes, I realise that your eyes cant actually light up when you are blinded...)<br><br>I know this is very mana costly and time consuming to do (and to maintain on them for that matter), and I realise that tests have been don e as to the effectiveness of these raised stats... but dont you just love the ability to make that humble old warrior feel like he's now the greatest warlord that ever walked. <br><br>Well, I just get all warm and fuzzy when I see it, cause I think *that* is the real fun in playing a shaman and I reckon there are a lot of people out there that just dont fully understand what we can REALLY do.<br><br>I just wanted to get that off my chest. We gotta get our kicks from something&nbsp;&nbsp;8)<br><br>Buffing with the best of them,<br>&nbsp;<br>Nekkarn<br>Uriens Spirithand<br>Uzurpa<br>(Morell Thule)</td></tr>
